  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem is a geometric packing/optimization problem. I will delegate the task of designing a non-overlapping rectangle generation strategy to a helper, then synthesize the final code.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "geometry_strategy_designer",
      "instructions": "Propose a robust algorithm for generating N non-overlapping axis-aligned rectangles within a 10000x10000 grid, where each rectangle i must contain a specific point (xi, yi) and attempt to approximate a target area ri. Consider strategies like a randomized greedy approach, a coordinate-based subdivision (like a k-d tree or quadtree approach), or a sweep-line approach to ensure no overlaps while maximizing area. The strategy must be simple enough to implement in a single Python script and handle the constraint that rectangles must stay within [0, 10000] bounds."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "I will take the proposed geometric strategy and implement it into a complete, valid Python script (main.py) that reads the input N and the N lines of (xi, yi, ri), executes the strategy to produce N lines of (x1, y1, x2, y2), and ensures all constraints (no overlaps, within bounds, contains point) are strictly met."
}

